		"ItemTooltips"
		{
			"item_veil_of_discord"		"Early tankiness solution and magic damage amplification. Makes you almost much more unkillable in fights early on and makes your damage output stupidly high"
			"item_sange_and_yasha"		"More of a defensive replacement for Drum or KaYasha, usually good when you need some mobility and stats"
			"item_hurricane_pike"		"Additional mobility and cheap stats. Early Force Staff works well when you're playing against AoE silences, terrain lockdowns or struggle to get into attack range to enemy"
			"item_ultimate_scepter"		"Great addition to reduce cooldown of your ultimate and amplify your crowd controlling capabilities"
			"item_shivas_guard"		"Doubling down on your magic tank role by amplifying your armor, magic damage and increasing your crowd control abilities by standing in the middle of a fight"
			"item_butterfly"		"Great addition for hybrid core. It also allowes you to become a decent damage dealer and pusher. It's also a great addition to +120 damage talent"
			"item_greater_crit"		"Nice addition to Buttterfly if you're playing against tanky cores or want to burst enemies down"
			"item_assault"		"More of an utility replacement for both Butterfly and Shiva's Guard. It helps with both tankiness, pushing and physical damage output, while also fitting theme of a walking tank"
			"item_crimson_guard"		"Against high attack speed cores, high physical damage lineups or summons"
			"item_lotus_orb"		"Against light disables (like slows and silences) in case you're not the only one struggling from them"
			"item_sheepstick"		"Additional reliable lockdown"
			"item_black_king_bar"		"Against hard disables and silences (if lotus doesn't work)"
			"item_mjollnir"		"Great DPS item for hybrid tank core transition"
		}
